Dilogue:-
show()
showmodel()
close()


dialog tag:-
----------

-> HTML provides special tag called <dialog> to display the content as a separate dialog box.

-> Inside the dialog tag, we can add any html tags that  you want to display in dialog.

Usage
-------
<dialog>
//required content
</dialog>

Methods
~~~~~~~~
1.show()
2.showmodel()
3.close()

<!-- Create a web page to display login form using dialog box -->
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
		<script >
		function f1() {
			var obj=document.getElementById('d1');
			// obj.show();
			obj.showModel();
		}
		function f2() {
			var obj = document.getElementById('d1');
			obj.close();
		}
	</script>
	<title></title>
</head>
<body >
	<h3>Welcome to HTML5</h3>
	<hr>
	<input type="button" onclick="f1();" value="UserLogin">
	<dialog id='d1'>
		<form action="Login.jsp" method="post">
			user Id: <input type="text" name="t1"><br><br>
			Password:<input type="Password" name="t2">
			<br><br>
			<input type="submit" value="Login">
			<input type="button" onclick="f2()" value="Cancel">
		</form>
	</dialog>

</body>
</html>




Multi-media tags in HTML5
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

-> HTML5 provides separate tags to play video and audio files.

1.<video> tag
2.<audio> tag
3.<source> tag

Implementation
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

1.<video> tag

<video id="video1">
	<source src="filename" type="video/mp4">
</video>

-------------------------------------------------------------------

2.<audio> tag
~~~~~~~~~~~~~

	<audio id="audio1" controls>
		<source src="filename" type="audio/mp3">
	</audio>

------------------------------------------------------------------


Attributes
~~~~~~~~~~

1.controls
2.poster
3.muted 
4.loop
5.height
6.width

------------------------------------------------------------------------

Methods: Programming related items
	
	-> play()
	-> pause()

------------------------------------------------------------------------

